llow the Semantics rules from flutter.md. They use `GestureDetector(onTapDown: .
..)` with `Semantics(identifier: ..., label: ..., button: true, container: true)
`. This is correct.\n\n8. **No use of `Color(0xFF...)` in formal widgets** - The
formal widgets in `flutter-widgets/` use `Tokens.xxx` or `DesignTokens.xxx`. Goo
d.\n\n9. **MANIFEST.md is comprehensive** - It includes migration steps, token p
roposals, widgetbook requirements. Good.\n\n10. **The PR includes visual assets*
* - Golden files (PNG) are included. Good.\n\n11. **`preview.dart` uses hardcode
d colors and `ElevatedButton`/`OutlinedButton`** - But MANIFEST.md explicitly do
cuments this as a self-contained preview file that may differ from formal widget
s. This is acceptable per the documented disclaimer.\n\n12. **PRD and docs updat
es** - The `prd/v1-matching.md` changes are just formatting and fixing the desig
n asset link from issue-4 to issue-43. The `matching-wireframe.md` is a new doc 
in the proper location. These are appropriate for a design PR.\n\nLet me reconsi
der the blocking issues:\n\nFor #1 (golden tests can\'t compile): This is indeed
blocking because the PR claims to include golden tests as visual proof, but they
